          id: 360029502031,
          title: 'Sending a check',
          sectionId: 360004817632,
          body:
            '<p> </p>\n<p class="p1"><strong>How to send a check:</strong></p>\n<ol class="ol1">\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Go to the<strong> Banking tab</strong> and click<strong> Send Check</strong>\n</li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Click<strong> +Recipent</strong> to add a new recipient <strong>or</strong> choose from your list of recipients </li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Enter the name of the recipient (<em><strong>Note:</strong></em> If you toggle "This is a business" you\'ll have to enter the account number) </li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Enter the<strong> address</strong> you are sending the check to and click <strong>Add recipient</strong>\n</li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Pick the recipient and enter the<strong> amount</strong> of funds you would like to send</li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Leave an optional memo</li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Review and confirm the provided information (delivery date will be provided on this screen!)</li>\n<li style="font-weight: 400;">Check is on the way!</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Then just review and confirm the information you entered.<strong> The delivery date of your check will also appear on this screen.</strong></p>\n<p>Once you confirm all the info, your check will be on its way. If you want, you\'ll then have the option to send another check at the same time.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p class="p1"> </p>',
