      id: 360001226391,
      title: '"Unsuccessful HTTP Response"',
      sectionId: 115000397452,
      body:
        '<h2><strong><span class="wysiwyg-font-size-large">What does this mean?</span></strong></h2>\n<p data-id="block-ember14250" data-generated-at="15046543992150.3973733225362801" data-align="left">Honestly, it\'s hard to say -- you may see this message for many reasons and at different times.</p>\n<p data-id="block-ember14250" data-generated-at="15046543992150.3973733225362801" data-align="left">As weird as it may sound, all this error message really means is that the app on your mobile device could not successfully "talk" to the servers at Dave H.Q. </p>\n<h2><strong><span class="wysiwyg-font-size-large">What should you do?</span></strong></h2>\n<p data-id="block-ember14254" data-generated-at="15046543992150.060172137040933826" data-align="left">Usually, taking a break and trying again later will resolve most issues, but occasionally, it could be an indication of a bug or larger issue. </p>\n<p data-id="block-ember14256" data-generated-at="15046543992160.7813779641676595" data-align="left">If the problem lasts for over 24 hours, <strong><a href="https://support.dave.com/hc/en-us/requests/new">message</a></strong> our customer support and we\'ll do our best to sort it out. </p>',
