          title: '"Current account balance must be greater than -$75."',
          sectionId: 115000397452,
          body:
            '<h2><strong>What does this mean?</strong></h2>\n<p>We found that most users with more than -$75 in their bank accounts were unable to pay us back successfully on their next paycheck. </p>\n<p>To help us and our users avoid nasty Non-Sufficient Funds fees, we decided to implement this restriction to keep your balances safe. </p>\n<h2><strong>What should you do? </strong></h2>\n<p>If you\'re back below -$75 and need to avoid an overdraft, go ahead and request again! </p>\n<p class="intercom-align-left"><img src="https://support.dave.com/hc/article_attachments/360004181171/Screen_Shot_2018-04-30_at_8.17.11_AM.png" alt="Screen_Shot_2018-04-30_at_8.17.11_AM.png"></p>',
