          id: 360012711771,
          title: "I can't identify any reliable income",
          sectionId: 115000397452,
          body:
            '<h2 class="intercom-align-left"><strong>What does this mean? </strong></h2>\n<p class="intercom-align-left">It looks like we weren\'t able to find consistent income in your checking account to qualify you for a regular advance.</p>\n<p class="intercom-align-left">Either your income didn\'t meet our <a href="https://support.dave.com/hc/en-us/articles/360016519532?flash_digest=b01e03347a5a3484e1d168b83fb785c16d7eef19"><strong>advance income requirements</strong></a>, or there\'s something wonky going on with your bank account (like inconsistent paydays or a delayed direct deposit) -- which we can help you out with!</p>\n<h2 class="intercom-align-left"><strong>What can you do? </strong></h2>\n<p class="intercom-align-left"><strong>1.</strong> Make sure your income meets our advance requirements outlined <strong><a href="https://support.dave.com/hc/en-us/articles/360016519532?flash_digest=b01e03347a5a3484e1d168b83fb785c16d7eef19">HERE</a></strong>. </p>\n<p class="intercom-align-left">If you don\'t meet our income requirements <em>yet</em>, you can still manually <strong><a href="https://support.dave.com/hc/en-us/articles/360002358331-Adding-income">add your income</a></strong> in the app for budgeting purposes and might still qualify for a smaller advance amount. </p>\n<p class="intercom-align-left"><strong>2. </strong><a href="https://support.dave.com/hc/en-us/requests/new"><strong>Message us</strong></a> if you meet our income requirements and you\'re still having trouble. Sometimes, accounts just need some old school human help and we\'re here for you.  </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>\n<p> </p>',
